r, George Feldenkreis, founder of the company, who now serves as executive chairman.Over the years, Oscar Feldenkreis has been involved in all aspects of the apparel retailer’s operations: he was named president and chief operating officer in February 1993 and was elected vice chairman in March 2005.In April, he became chief executive officer as part of the publicly traded apparel company’s succession plan. Mr. Feldenkreis said he shifted his focus to strategy and taking the company to the next level, which is building Perry Ellis into a global brand.To be successful today, he said, you have to be global, because people are increasingly shopping online as well as strongly identifying with the brand they want to buy. To meet customers’ changing tastes and shopping habits, Mr. Feldenkreis said, Perry Ellis International is adding more brands, growing its e-commerce platform and opening up more retail stores.In fact, the Original Penguin store at Miami International Airport is to open today (6/30) in Concourse D. At the end of the day, though, Mr. Feldenkreis said his biggest accomplishment is identifying with the others working at Perry Ellis International, who include each one of the company’s 2,400 associates. He said his instincts and vision can be good, but the company would not be where it is today without its “good team.” Mr. Feldenkreis said it’s much like the legacy of any great sport franchise, which he describes as all about the culture, passion and execution. In particular, Mr. Feldenkreis said he attributes his achievement to having his father next to him from the day he started working for the company. He sat in his father’s office, listening to him and how he conducted business, which he said was the greatest education he could have received.Miami Today reporter Susan Danseyar interviewed Mr. Feldenkreis in his office at Perry Ellis International headquarters.To read the full article and the rest of the Miami Today issue, subscribe to e-MIAMI TODAY, an exact replica of the printed edition.Share This PostTweet  AdvertisementRelated ArticlesRobert Rodriguez: Guiding NatCom to produce 1,500…Juan Acosta: Consolidates Viacom productions in new…Rene Ruiz: Fashion designer targets Hialeah…Profile: Stuart ChaseIra Coleman: To run international law firm McDermott…Eric Mendelson: Oversees high-flying aerospace…Ana-Marie Codina Barlick: Creating 120-acre Downtown…Martin Mendez: Spearheads IT change in health care,…Profile: Serge ElkinerRamona Messore: Develops a very different Saks for…Most Popular  92-story downtown tower OK’d for Miami’s skyline   Transportation planners factoring in autonomous vehicles   36-story tower replacing City Hall (the restaurant)   Hyatt lease tied to Brickell tunnel staging area   Miami to get a free fire station in Brickell   Restoration of Miami Marine Stadium a $40 million ticket   Professionals learn of plans to grow Miami International Airport   Mayor’s about-face on transit modes is compelling logic   Brightline rail will start with deeply discounted fares   Site pinpointed for new civil courthouse in Miami   Advertisement  Advertisement AdvertisementBreaking NewsArts & CultureBusiness & FinanceCommunitiesEducationFilmingFilming in MiamiFYI MiamiGovernmentHealthcareProfileReal EstateTransportationFront PageNewsBreaking NewsArts & CultureBusiness & FinanceCommunitiesEducationFilmingFilming in MiamiFYI MiamiGovernmentHealthcareProfileReal EstateTransportationOpinionCalendarArchives © 2017 Miami Today. All Rights Reserved. E-Paper | Terms and Conditions | Site Map | Privacy Policy |            
